<promed@promedmail.org>
[Actually, the US Center for Disease Control estimates that 73 000 cases
and 61 deaths occur in the USA annually. Lin et al. (J Microbiol Immunol
Infect 2001 Mar;34(1):17-24) have shown a prevalence of _E. coli_ O157:H7
of 0.13 percent in fresh bovine fecal samples, and of 2.6 percent in dairy
cattle in Taiwan. In a survey of specimens from 1280 patients presenting
with acute diarrhea from 1994-1996, Lee et al. failed to isolate any _E.
coli_ O157:H7 (J Microbiol Immunol Infect 1997 Feb;30(1):55-59). There are
no cases listed for Taiwan on the GIDEON database. This may be the first
recorded case for Taiwan as indicated in the article above. - Mod.ES]
